Example Ex51: An inductive heating assembly for conveying and inductively heating an aerosol-forming liquid, wherein the heating assembly comprises:





at least one liquid-conveying susceptor assembly according to any one of the preceding examples;

at least one induction source configured and arranged to generate an alternating magnetic field in a heating section of the at least one liquid-conveying susceptor assembly, in particular in a heating section of the non-grid portion.

Example Ex57: An aerosol-generating article for use with an inductively heating aerosol-generating device, the article comprising:





at least one reservoir for storing aerosol-forming liquid, wherein the liquid reservoir comprises an outlet;

at least one liquid-conveying susceptor assembly according to any one of examples Ex1 to Ex50 for delivering aerosol-forming liquid from the liquid reservoir through the outlet into a region outside the liquid reservoir.
